data.description: This well-maintained, owner-occupied home is nestled in the sought-after community of Copper Ridge.  This Valrico community requires only a low HOA, and no CDD.  The home sits on a cul-de-sac street lined with sidewalks.  The home's open floor plan and vaulted ceilings usher natural light into the home from every direction.  The kitchen is in the heart of the home and offers solid wood cabinets, a large closet pantry, and sits adjacent to the breakfast nook.  The oven and refrigerator are new, and the kitchen appliances, washer and dryer all stay.  The water heater is also new.  The floors are matching tile, throughout.  The roof is approximately six years old.  New sliding doors and new windows have been installed, improving the home's energy efficiency and reducing outside noise, with hurricane shutters available for all windows.  The screened back lanai is a must for Florida living!  The white vinyl fully fenced back yard includes a variety of fruit trees and plants.  Even better, there are no back yard neighbors, as this home backs up to a fenced-off community-maintained common area.  The home is near Interstate 75, Interstate 4, and the downtown Tampa area.  Schedule your showing today and fall in love with your new home!  Note: The Ring doorbell stays with the home.  Sellers will need 60 days to close.
